Jacobi Prior for Supervised Learning

Sourish Das and Shouvik Sardar

Problem Statement

library(microbenchmark)

source(file="utility.R")
df = read.csv(file="SBAnational_v2.csv",header=T)

Data preprocessing

df$Disbursement_Gross_std= scale(log(df$Disbursement_Gross+1))
df$Term_std = scale(log(df$Term+1))
df$NoEmp_std = scale(log(df$NoEmp+1))

Split the data into train and test

n = nrow(df)
m = floor(n*0.7)
set.seed(3725)
id_str = sort(sample(1:n,m,replace = F))

df_train = df[id_str,]
df_test = df[-id_str,]
rm(list = c("df"))

GLM

time_glm = microbenchmark(
  fit_glm <- glm(Default~New+RealEstate +Disbursement_Gross_std +Term_std+NoEmp_std ,data=df_train
                 ,family = binomial())
  ,times = 10 )

X = model.matrix(fit_glm)
y = fit_glm$y
dum=glm(Default~New+RealEstate +Disbursement_Gross_std +Term_std+NoEmp_std ,data=df_test
                 ,family = binomial())

X = model.matrix(fit_glm)
y = fit_glm$y

X_test = model.matrix(dum)
y_test = dum$y

rm(dum) ## Remove dum

Collect \(\hat{\beta}\) and predict Default in test dataset.

beta_hat_glm = coef(fit_glm)

Lasso

fit_lasso<-function(){
  fit <- cv.glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial",alpha=1)
  lambda_hat <- fit$lambda.min
  fit <- glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", lambda = lambda_hat,alpha=1)
  return(fit)
}
time_lasso = microbenchmark(
            fit_Lasso<-fit_lasso()
            ,times = 10
          )

predict Default in test dataset.

p_hat_lasso = predict(fit_Lasso,newx=X_test,type="response")

df_test$denie_lasso=0
df_test$denie_lasso[p_hat_lasso>0.5]=1

Calculate accuracy and utility of prediction

conf_table_lasso = table(Denie=df_test$denie_lasso
                    ,Default=df_test$Default)
acc_lasso = sum(diag(conf_table_lasso))/sum(conf_table_lasso)*100


util_lasso =util_calc(denie=df_test$denie_lasso
                       ,default=df_test$Default
                       ,value=df_test$Disbursement_Gross)


rmse_lasso = sqrt(mean((y_test-p_hat_lasso)^2))

c(acc_naive,acc_glm,acc_lasso)

Ridge

fit_ridge<-function(){
  fit <- cv.glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial",alpha=0)
  lambda_hat <- fit$lambda.min
  fit <- glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", lambda = lambda_hat,alpha=0)
  return(fit)
}

time_ridge = microbenchmark(
            fit_Ridge<-fit_ridge()
            ,times = 10
          )

Predict Default in test dataset using the Ridge model

p_hat_ridge = predict(fit_Ridge,newx=X_test,type="response")
df_test$denie_ridge=0
df_test$denie_ridge[p_hat_ridge>0.5]=1

Elastic Net

fit_EN<-function(){
  fit <- cv.glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial",alpha=0.5)
  lambda_hat <- fit$lambda.min
  fit <- glmnet(X, y, family = "binomial", lambda = lambda_hat,alpha=0.5)
  return(fit)
}

time_EN = microbenchmark(
  fit.EN<-fit_EN()
    ,times = 10
)

Predict Default in test dataset using the Elastic Net

p_hat_EN = predict(fit.EN,newx=X_test,type="response")

df_test$denie_EN=0

Jacobi Prior : Strategy 1

We choose \(a=b=5/10\)

a = 5/10
b = 5/10

x=seq(0,1,by=0.01)
plot(x,dbeta(x,a,b),type="l")

m=1
p=ncol(X)
eta_hat = log((y+a)/(b+m-y))
eta_hat = as.vector(eta_hat)

time_Jacob1<- microbenchmark(
    beta_hat_Jacobi1<- solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%t(X)%*%eta_hat
)

Predict Default in test datasets

z_hat_Jacobi1 = X_test%*%beta_hat_Jacobi1
p_hat_Jacobi1=exp(z_hat_Jacobi1)/(1+exp(z_hat_Jacobi1))

df_test$denie_Jacobi1=0
df_test$denie_Jacobi1[p_hat_Jacobi1>0.5]=1

Calculate accuracy and utility of the prediction

conf_table_Jacobi1 = table(Denie=df_test$denie_Jacobi1
                           ,Default=df_test$Default)
acc_Jacobi1 = sum(diag(conf_table_Jacobi1))/sum(conf_table_Jacobi1)*100

util_Jacobi1 = util_calc(denie=df_test$denie_Jacobi1
                         ,default=df_test$Default
                         ,value=df_test$Disbursement_Gross)

rmse_Jacobi1 = sqrt(mean((y_test-p_hat_Jacobi1)^2))

c(acc_naive,acc_glm,acc_lasso,acc_ridge,acc_EN,acc_Jacobi1)

Jacobi Prior: Bayesian Optimisation

Use Bayesian optimisation to estimate a and b

Jacobi_prior(0.4,0.8)
## $Score
## [1] 4.590078e-05
## 
## $Pred
## [1] 0
set.seed(56237)
time_Jacobi_BayesOpt<-microbenchmark(
  Opt_Res_BO <- BayesianOptimization(Jacobi_prior
                                  ,bound=list(a=c(0,1),b=c(0,1))
                                  ,init_grid_dt = NULL, init_points = 10
                                  , n_iter = 20
                                  ,acq = "poi", kappa = 2.576, eps = 0.01,
                                  verbose = FALSE) 
  ,times = 2
)
## 
##  Best Parameters Found: 
## Round = 6    a = 0.1620557   b = 0.3603256   Value = 4.59574e-05 
## 
##  Best Parameters Found: 
## Round = 21   a = 0.4597472   b = 0.7622321   Value = 4.593326e-05
a=Opt_Res_BO$Best_Par['a']
b=Opt_Res_BO$Best_Par['b']

Consolidate the Results

accuracy <- c(acc_glm,acc_lasso,acc_ridge
              ,acc_EN,acc_Jacobi1
              ,acc_Jacobi2,acc_Jacobi_sto
              ,acc_Jacobi_BO)
